@baseUrl = http://localhost:8002
@authUrl = http://localhost:8080/api/auth
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Login to get Token (Auth Service)
# Copy the 'accessToken' from the response and paste it below in the @token variable
POST {{authUrl}}/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
    "username": "testadmin",
    "password": "password123"
}

### Variable for Token (Replace with your actual token after login)
@token = YOUR_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE

### 2. Create a Grade (Requires ADMIN Role)
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "student_id": "S1001",
    "subject": "Mathematics",
    "value": 18.5
}

### 3. Create Another Grade
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "student_id": "S1001",
    "subject": "Physics",
    "value": 16.0
}

### 4. Create Third Grade
POST {{baseUrl}}/grades/
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "student_id": "S1001",
    "subject": "Chemistry",
    "value": 17.5
}

### 5. Get All Grades for a Student
GET {{baseUrl}}/grades/S1001
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Get Average Grade for a Student
GET {{baseUrl}}/grades/average/S1001
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Update a Grade (Requires ADMIN Role)
# Replace {grade_id} with actual grade ID from previous responses
PUT {{baseUrl}}/grades/{grade_id}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{
    "value": 19.0
}

### 8. Delete a Grade (Requires ADMIN Role)
# Replace {grade_id} with actual grade ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/grades/{grade_id}
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 9. Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### 10. Root Endpoint
GET {{baseUrl}}/
